Subjects were provided with customized dietary plans prepared by one of the researchers (A.A.A.) for the length of the study. In order to facilitate weight loss, energy consumption was set so that subjects remained in a caloric deficit. The determination of energy intake was based on the Mifflin-St. Jeor Equation, which is considered an accurate formula for estimating resting metabolic rate [20]. The formula is as follows:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
