Normality assumptions were checked using a one-sample Kolmogorov-Smirnov test; all data was found to meet normality assumptions. Independent t-tests were used to assess differences in baseline measurements between groups as well as energy and macronutrient intake over the length of the study period. Cohen’s D effect sizes were calculated for all pre- to post-study outcome measures using the following formula:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
